title: NASA, Boeing to Host Media Briefing, Provide Starliner Update
summary: NASA and Boeing will host a media teleconference at 2 p.m. EDT Wednesday, March 29, to provide an update on the Crew Flight Test (CFT) of the CST-100 Starliner spacecraft to the International Space Station.

title: NASA Names Two Diversity Champions for Agency
summary: NASA Administrator Bill Nelson announced Monday he is taking additional steps forward to advance diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility (DEIA) at the agency. title: NASA Associate Administrator Announces Retirement, Replacement Announced
summary: NASA Associate Administrator, Kathy Lueders announces retirement; Ken Bowersoz announced as new head of Space Operations.

title: Changes Ahead as NASA’s Human Spaceflight Head Plans Retirement
summary: Kathryn Lueders, associate administrator of NASA’s Space Operations Mission Directorate, announced Monday she will retire from the agency at the end of April. Lueders’ current deputy and astronaut, Ken Bowersox, will become the new head of Space Operations, effective Monday, May 1.

title: Blue Origin provides a detailed analysis of its launch failure
summary: The company says it intends to return to flight "soon."

title: Inflation, high demand driving up launch prices
summary: A tight launch market, coupled with high inflation, has driven up launch prices in the last year, putting a squeeze on customers.

title: Remote sensing companies try to capture bigger piece of satellite imaging market
summary: Maxar, Planet and BlackSky are working to expand their offerings beyond optical imagery.

title: ABL Space Secures $60M USSF/USAF Demo Contract
summary: ABL Space Systems has secured a $60 million contract from the US Space Force and US Air Force.

title: Canada Commits To ISS 2030 Extension
summary: Canada has formally committed to an extension of the International Space Station to 2030.

title: OneWeb Completes V1 Constellation With India Launch
summary: The ISRO successfully launched 26 OneWeb internet satellites, completing OneWeb's first generation constellation.
